From d425952c23ba19507349d2e3aa3c8aa1bca1fbd1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ramesh Mandal <ramesh@6epixels.com>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 18:25:02 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(privacy): server-enforced visibility, community
 discovery, complete-end private mode

Server:
- visibility carried in hello + live 'visibility' event; roster
  broadcasts contain PUBLIC users only - private users never leave
  the server
- dm rejected when sender is private (sender_private) or recipient is
  private/offline (recipient_unavailable); the two recipient cases are
  indistinguishable to prevent presence leaks
- typing from private users silently dropped
- zero message retention: pure relay, nothing stored or logged
- committed test suite (pnpm --filter @tabcom/backend test): 7 privacy
  tests covering discovery, both barriers, typing, live switching,
  and presence-leak resistance

Extension:
- CommunitiesView = live discovery directory of public online users;
  private mode shows a complete-end explainer with one-tap Go Public
- Settings visibility toggle pushes to server, takes effect instantly
- ChatView: composer replaced by privacy notice while private (server
  enforces regardless); system notices rendered as centered chips
- dm_error -> local system message ('not delivered / you're private')
- 'system' message kind (local-only, never relayed)
- WXT_REALTIME_URL env support for LAN / cross-device testing
